&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 - Staff Nurse : 1 Year Fixed Term Contract&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Fortuneswell ward is a 17 bed in-patient ward specialising in the care of adults with cancer and haematological disease. The ward commonly manages patients who are admitted with acute problems relating to their cancer or its treatment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for a band 5 Registered Nurse who is motivated and enthusiastic with a genuine interest in caring for patients with cancer. A good knowledge base of oncology and/or haemato-oncology is desirable, however, candidates who demonstrate a true interest in the specialty are welcome to apply and full training will be given. There is an excellent opportunity to develop on this ward with a great training programme in haematology/oncology/and chemotherapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to work shifts and be flexible to meet the needs of the service. You must possess excellent communication skills and will ideally be competent at venepuncture and cannulation although this is not essential. Candidates who lack specialist qualifications must be willing to undertake relevant training and education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sarah Burrows, Ward Manager Tel: 01305-253345 Email: Sarah.burrows@dchft.nhs.uk &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;or Nikki Wilson Deputy Ward Sister Nicola.wilson@dchft.nhs.uk Tel: 01305 253342&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
